.TH "i40e_mirrorrule_op" 9 "i40e_mirrorrule_op" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_mirrorrule_op \- Internal helper function to add/delete mirror rule
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "i40e_status" i40e_mirrorrule_op
.BI "(struct i40e_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 opcode "  ","
.BI "u16 sw_seid "  ","
.BI "u16 rule_type "  ","
.BI "u16 id "  ","
.BI "u16 count "  ","
.BI "__le16 *mr_list "  ","
.BI "struct i40e_asq_cmd_details *cmd_details "  ","
.BI "u16 *rule_id "  ","
.BI "u16 *rules_used "  ","
.BI "u16 *rules_free "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the hw struct
.IP "opcode" 12
AQ opcode for add or delete mirror rule
.IP "sw_seid" 12
Switch SEID (to which rule refers)
.IP "rule_type" 12
Rule Type (ingress/egress/VLAN)
.IP "id" 12
Destination VSI SEID or Rule ID
.IP "count" 12
length of the list
.IP "mr_list" 12
list of mirrored VSI SEIDs or VLAN IDs
.IP "cmd_details" 12
pointer to command details structure or NULL
.IP "rule_id" 12
Rule ID returned from FW
.IP "rules_used" 12
Number of rules used in internal switch
.IP "rules_free" 12
Number of rules free in internal switch
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add/Delete a mirror rule to a specific switch. Mirror rules are supported for
VEBs/VEPA elements only
